Reasoning: The paper focuses on the analysis of Open Access policies and their impact on the deposit of research outputs in repositories. The most relevant arXiv CS sub-category is cs.DL (Digital Libraries), which deals with the management, organization, and dissemination of digital information. Other relevant sub-categories include cs.CY (Computational Geometry), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), and cs.CL (Computation and Language), as they all involve the processing and analysis of large amounts of data and information.
